reclaimed it from
ISIS militants this week.

17:43.763 --> 17:49.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But even with the government
victory, thousands
of people now languish in the
summer desert

17:49.168 --> 17:52.271 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
heat, with almost nothing to
sustain them.

17:52.305 --> 17:54.607 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Special correspondent Jane Arraf
reports.

17:54.640 --> 18:01.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE ARRAF: This is Fallujah the
morning Iraqi
security forces took back the
city from ISIS.

18:01.380 --> 18:07.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Months before ISIS declared an
Islamic State
in Mosul two years ago, it
seized this city.

18:07.853 --> 18:14.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Iraqi security forces, backed by
U.S. airstrikes,
recaptured Fallujah. It took a
month of fighting.

18:14.160 --> 18:20.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. tried to make sure
Iraq's Shia militias
backed by Iran were kept on the
sidelines

18:20.366 --> 18:22.635 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the battle for this Sunni
city.

18:22.668 --> 18:28.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But as Iraqi government forces
moved on after
securing the Jolan neighborhood,
militia fighters

18:28.874 --> 18:33.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
