accusing Fallujah
of being in bed with ISIS.

18:39.118 --> 18:44.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Don't take pictures of this," a
fighter tells
us, near a burning house. They
tell us to

18:44.690 --> 18:48.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
go back to the Iraqi special
forces we have
come to see.

18:48.094 --> 18:49.628 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: PBS.

18:49.662 --> 18:51.564 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: PBS.

18:51.597 --> 18:57.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE ARRAF: U.S.-trained Iraqi
special forces
led the assault into the south
side of Fallujah.

18:57.470 --> 19:03.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First Sergeant Amar Ahmed Jassim
says the
elite forces are grateful for
their U.S. training.

19:03.943 --> 19:08.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
1ST SGT. AMAR AHMED JASSIM, Iraq
(through
translator): America, since the
fall of Saddam

19:08.080 --> 19:13.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
until now, has not abandoned
Iraq. Up until
now, they provide air support.
After all,

19:13.686 --> 19:15.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they are our friends. They won't
abandon us.

19:15.888 --> 19:20.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE ARRAF: Although the main
battle is over,
Iraqi helicopters are still
attacking remaining

19:20.659 --> 19:22.561 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ISIS fighters.

19:22.595 --> 19:28.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is just a couple of hours
after Iraqi
security forces have declared
Fallujah completely

19:28.367 --> 19:34.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
liberated. Two weeks ago, they
said they had
taken back complete control of
the city, but

19:34.140 --> 19:39.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
