47:45.029 --> 47:51.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LESLEY M.M. BLUME: Sexual
rivalry, fistfights,
you name it, it happened. And it
wasn't a

47:51.602 --> 47:56.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very good situation for anybody
involved,
except for Hemingway, who in
turn saw this

47:56.640 --> 48:00.978 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as desperately needed material
to stage a
breakthrough novelistically.

48:01.011 --> 48:04.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And then suddenly
he had a
lot of material.

48:04.248 --> 48:09.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LESLEY M.M. BLUME: Well, he
literally took
the events that had transpired
in Pamplona

48:09.286 --> 48:11.856 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and Paris and translated them
onto paper.

48:11.889 --> 48:15.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: To the point
where I saw you
say some people wondered whether
it was actual

48:15.126 --> 48:18.329 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
