out a year
later, and said, this is nothing
but a report

48:34.145 --> 48:36.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on what happened. How can he
pass this off
as fiction?

48:36.781 --> 48:41.318 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Now, this is
Hemingway before
he was Hemingway, right? This is
-- he's all

48:41.352 --> 48:43.287 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of 25 years old at the time.

48:43.320 --> 48:45.055 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LESLEY M.M. BLUME: Right.

48:45.089 --> 48:49.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, Hemingway is a baby when
he turns up
in Paris, but he's an ambitious
baby. And

48:49.260 --> 48:53.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
