52:00.951 --> 52:04.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER WEINER, Author, "Hungry
Heart": They
say that the happiest day of a
writer's life

52:04.555 --> 52:09.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is the day he or she gets to go
home to tell
mom and dad that the book that
they have written

52:09.126 --> 52:14.131 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
is actually going to be
published, to be sold
in stores, and read by
strangers, and out

52:14.164 --> 52:15.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the world.

52:15.866 --> 52:21.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I assume that's true for every
writer who
didn't call her first book "Good
in Bed."

52:21.105 --> 52:26.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I will never forget my mom
hugging me, and
then pulling back to ask, "So
what's the title?"

52:26.343 --> 52:31.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
